♫  The road ahead is long, 
 and there is an unquenchable light in my heart  ♫

13
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:29,239
♫  Because someone is waiting for me  ♫

14
00:01:29,239 --> 00:01:36,918
♫  There is one person who will complete the dream  ♫

15
00:01:36,919 --> 00:01:39,019
   

16
00:01:39,020 --> 00:01:43,059
   

17
00:01:43,059 --> 00:01:44,939
   

18
00:01:44,940 --> 00:01:47,940
   

19
00:01:48,535 --> 00:01:51,996
If His Majesty were to know that she's a problematic person,

20
00:01:51,996 --> 00:01:54,875
I'm afraid she'll be removed.

21
00:01:56,136 --> 00:01:59,556
Lord Ding, what are your thoughts on this?

22
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:02,855
Miss Sun,

23
00:02:02,856 --> 00:02:05,215
what you have done is unethical.

24
00:02:05,215 --> 00:02:07,875
Yet you dare to ask for my opinion.

25
00:02:11,775 --> 00:02:15,076
Your Majesty, I shall take my leave.

26
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:22,590
   

27
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:34,180
   

28
00:02:44,615 --> 00:02:48,155
Greetings, Your Majesty. I'm Mu Zhuohua, the Director of the Ministry of Revenue.

29
00:02:48,155 --> 00:02:51,656
Mu Zhuohua, do you plead guilty?

30
00:02:53,655 --> 00:02:57,934
Your Majesty, what is it that I am guilty of?

31
00:02:59,215 --> 00:03:02,155
Observer Sun, tell her.

32
00:03:02,155 --> 00:03:04,496
What exactly is Mu Zhuohua guilty of?

33
00:03:04,496 --> 00:03:08,156
You changed your birthplace from Huaizhou to Yanzhou.

34
00:03:08,856 --> 00:03:11,196
Deceiving the emperor is a grave offense.

35
00:03:11,196 --> 00:03:14,174
Mu Zhuohua, you still pretend not to know.

36
00:03:14,174 --> 00:03:16,696
 My change of origins was like a hanging knife. 

37
00:03:16,696 --> 00:03:19,456
 I didn't expect it to fall on me today. 

38
00:03:22,615 --> 00:03:24,215
Mu Zhuohua,

39
00:03:24,215 --> 00:03:27,695
the last time, I gave you 30 floggings as punishment.

40
00:03:27,696 --> 00:03:30,616
How should I punish you this time?

41
00:03:30,616 --> 00:03:33,695
Do you have anything else to say?

42
00:03:36,976 --> 00:03:38,576
I...

43
00:03:39,935 --> 00:03:43,535
I... I have nothing to say.

44
00:03:43,535 --> 00:03:45,496
Guards!

45
00:03:45,496 --> 00:03:47,036
Take her away!

46
00:03:50,276 --> 00:03:51,876
 Wait! 

47
00:04:03,495 --> 00:04:05,295
Down.

48
00:04:16,736 --> 00:04:19,696
Greetings, Your Majesty and Lord Ding.

49
00:04:32,616 --> 00:04:33,935
Your Majesty,

50
00:04:33,936 --> 00:04:37,755
Mu Zhuohua is unworthy of her title as Tanhua.

51
00:04:37,755 --> 00:04:40,055
She is originally from Huaizhou, Jiangnan.

52
00:04:40,056 --> 00:04:43,114
She is the seventh daughter of Mu Rong, whose family is the richest in Jiangnan.

53
00:04:43,114 --> 00:04:45,316
Her real name is Mu Qi.

54
00:04:45,316 --> 00:04:49,215
She took the metropolitan examination by changing her birthplace.

55
00:04:49,215 --> 00:04:52,156
I can explain, Your Majesties.

56
00:04:52,156 --> 00:04:55,736
I changed my birthplace because I didn't have a choice.

57
00:04:55,736 --> 00:04:59,356
I am indeed from Huaizhou.

58
00:05:00,056 --> 00:05:02,575
At the time, I was being forced to marry Zhuang Wenfeng.

59
00:05:02,576 --> 00:05:04,376
I refused to do so.

60
00:05:04,376 --> 00:05:09,334
I was determined to pass the imperial examination and become a scholar.

61
00:05:09,334 --> 00:05:14,655
I only changed my birthplace to Yanzhou out... out of desperation.

62
00:05:14,655 --> 00:05:17,414
Even so, it is a crime of deceiving the emperor.

63
00:05:17,415 --> 00:05:20,836
Mu Zhuohua gained the title of Tanhua with her talents.

64
00:05:20,836 --> 00:05:26,596
However, due to the change in her birthplace, she has been walking on thin ice and living in fear.

65
00:05:26,596 --> 00:05:28,135
She was afraid that if it got exposed,

66
00:05:28,136 --> 00:05:32,095
everything she did for the people of Southern Chen would turn to ashes.

67
00:05:32,816 --> 00:05:34,695
What about you, Miss Sun?

68
00:05:35,295 --> 00:05:37,355
You were born with advantages.

69
00:05:37,355 --> 00:05:40,635
You made it to a political observer with the merits of your ancestors.

70
00:05:40,635 --> 00:05:44,276
However, you never thought of ways to benefit the people.

71
00:05:44,276 --> 00:05:48,195
Instead, you are acting shamelessly and meanly for your own gain.

72
00:05:48,195 --> 00:05:49,815
May I ask Miss Sun.

73
00:05:49,816 --> 00:05:54,555
Do you feel worthy of being a political observer in the Ministry of Revenue?

74
00:05:56,616 --> 00:05:57,915
Your Majesties,

75
00:05:57,915 --> 00:06:01,534
I gained this position according to the system of the court.

76
00:06:01,535 --> 00:06:03,114
I have never deceived the emperor.

77
00:06:03,114 --> 00:06:05,015
That's enough!

78
00:06:05,015 --> 00:06:09,196
I was already aware that Mu Zhuohua changed her birthplace.

79
00:06:10,535 --> 00:06:12,396
How can that be?

80
00:06:15,636 --> 00:06:19,795
 I am now clear about Mu Zhuohua and the change of her birthplace. 

81
00:06:19,795 --> 00:06:23,895
 Emperor Brother, how do you plan to punish her? 

82
00:06:24,816 --> 00:06:28,315
 How do you want me to punish her? 

83
00:06:31,115 --> 00:06:33,335
 I dare not overstep my authority. 

84
00:06:33,335 --> 00:06:37,655
 It's just that passing the examination isn't easy for a lady. 

85
00:06:37,655 --> 00:06:42,755
 Moreover, Mu Zhuohua has exceptional character and abilities. 

86
00:06:42,755 --> 00:06:46,355
 I hope you can forgive her. 

87
00:06:49,215 --> 00:06:53,255
 It is rare to see you think so highly of someone. 

88
00:06:54,376 --> 00:06:59,515
 Mu Zhuohua's reason for changing her birthplace is justified. 

89
00:06:59,515 --> 00:07:05,616
 Furthermore, she is the right-hand woman whom I am planning to keep for the new emperor. 

90
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:11,575
 Don't worry. I value talent more than you do. 

91
00:07:13,435 --> 00:07:17,616
 I thank Your Majesty on Mu Zhuohua's behalf. 

92
00:07:18,895 --> 00:07:20,874
Lord Ding had informed me of this matter long ago.

93
00:07:20,874 --> 00:07:25,515
It was to show me if Tanhua Mu was really competent.

94
00:07:25,515 --> 00:07:28,956
The reason I sent her to Jiangnan was to see

95
00:07:28,956 --> 00:07:31,894
if she was able to turn the tide in her hometown.

96
00:07:31,895 --> 00:07:33,895
She has proven that she is capable of it.

97
00:07:33,895 --> 00:07:35,616
But you?

98
00:07:36,855 --> 00:07:39,616
If you really thought she deceived me,

99
00:07:39,616 --> 00:07:43,475
you should have come to me about it, but not the Dowager Empress.

100
00:07:43,975 --> 00:07:48,275
Don't forget that you are now not the Young Lady Sun

101
00:07:48,275 --> 00:07:51,075
but a political observer in the Ministry of Revenue.

102
00:07:53,655 --> 00:07:55,735
Please have mercy, Your Majesty!

103
00:07:55,735 --> 00:07:57,155
Have mercy?

104
00:07:57,155 --> 00:08:01,255
You have held this position for so long, yet you addressed yourself as a common person.

105
00:08:01,255 --> 00:08:02,795
Miss Sun,

106
00:08:02,795 --> 00:08:09,096
if you don't intend to be an official, why take up the position of a political observer?

107
00:08:12,376 --> 00:08:14,276
Yunyun was just...

108
00:08:17,415 --> 00:08:18,915
Mother,

109
00:08:18,915 --> 00:08:22,235
please stop interfering in politics.

110
00:08:24,936 --> 00:08:26,536
Sun Yunyun,

111
00:08:26,536 --> 00:08:28,955
since you have no intention to be an official,

112
00:08:28,955 --> 00:08:33,375
you can go home and be the young lady of the Sun family.

113
00:08:39,456 --> 00:08:43,474
As for Ms. Mu, deceiving was not your intention,

114
00:08:43,474 --> 00:08:45,714
but it was still wrong to change your birthplace.

115
00:08:45,714 --> 00:08:49,675
I'll deduct your salary for three months as your punishment.

116
00:08:49,675 --> 00:08:51,236
Yes, Your Majesty.

117
00:09:02,195 --> 00:09:04,195
I shall take my leave.

118
00:09:07,290 --> 00:09:09,550
   

119
00:09:34,675 --> 00:09:36,375
Still feeling scared?

120
00:09:39,096 --> 00:09:43,035
My Lord, changing my birthplace was enough to get me executed.

121
00:09:43,035 --> 00:09:45,554
I just came back from the gates of Hell.

122
00:09:45,554 --> 00:09:47,655
I'm obviously scared.

123
00:09:47,655 --> 00:09:49,755
I'm still feeling scared.

124
00:09:51,395 --> 00:09:55,150
My Lord, why didn't you tell me that

125
00:09:55,150 --> 00:09:59,460
that His Majesty was already aware of it?

126
00:10:00,216 --> 00:10:02,156
Only His Majesty needs to know.

127
00:10:02,156 --> 00:10:04,836
This matter cannot be disclosed.

128
00:10:04,836 --> 00:10:09,015
If it weren't for Miss Sun picking a fight today,

129
00:10:09,015 --> 00:10:14,756
His Majesty and I would have planned to take it to our graves.

130
00:10:16,256 --> 00:10:17,495
You are right.

131
00:10:17,496 --> 00:10:20,455
After all, I wasn't honest about this.

132
00:10:20,455 --> 00:10:25,856
I am really lucky that I am still alive.

133
00:10:27,216 --> 00:10:29,775
I can finally have a good sleep.

134
00:10:36,256 --> 00:10:38,156
Do you want to sleep?

135
00:10:42,216 --> 00:10:44,496
I won't sleep in your carriage.

136
00:10:53,175 --> 00:10:54,395
 My Lord! 

137
00:10:54,395 --> 00:10:56,194
 Xue Xiaotang is having another relapse. 

138
00:10:56,194 --> 00:10:57,794
 It seems unlikely for him to make it through this time. 

139
00:10:57,794 --> 00:11:00,135
 Imperial Physician Lu is doing his best to save him. 

140
00:11:02,055 --> 00:11:04,354
- Quickly return. 
 - Yes, My Lord.

141
00:11:11,835 --> 00:11:13,435
Hold him down.

142
00:11:13,435 --> 00:11:15,315
Imperial Physician Lu, I'll help you.

143
00:11:15,315 --> 00:11:16,915
Get the needle.

144
00:11:34,096 --> 00:11:36,175
He can't carry on like this.

145
00:11:36,175 --> 00:11:39,555
Imperial Physician Lu, I heard the Imperial Academy of Medicine has rare books.

146
00:11:39,555 --> 00:11:41,594
Please try to find another cure.

147
00:11:41,594 --> 00:11:44,435
All right, I will look through them right away.

148
00:12:06,056 --> 00:12:07,255
Miss Sun.

149
00:12:07,256 --> 00:12:08,556
Official Fang.

150
00:12:08,556 --> 00:12:10,455
Are you going home?

151
00:12:10,456 --> 00:12:12,916
I'm waiting for someone. You may go ahead.

152
00:12:12,916 --> 00:12:14,376
All right.

153
00:12:41,276 --> 00:12:44,016
Thank Official Mu for me.

154
00:12:44,016 --> 00:12:48,236
Thank her for looking after me as of late.

155
00:12:49,256 --> 00:12:53,015
It's just that dealing with so many men every day

156
00:12:53,016 --> 00:12:56,156
is not good for a lady's reputation.

157
00:12:56,156 --> 00:12:59,135
I didn't know any better at first and took the wrong path.

158
00:12:59,136 --> 00:13:02,935
Now that I've come to a realization, that means farewell.

159
00:13:08,336 --> 00:13:10,095
Stop, miss.

160
00:13:10,096 --> 00:13:12,096
No need to relay it.

161
00:13:14,256 --> 00:13:20,056
How many people have had a hard time walking this short journey?

162
00:13:20,056 --> 00:13:22,035
    
 Some people go straight to the top

163
00:13:22,035 --> 00:13:24,255
and still criticize others with a petty heart.

164
00:13:24,256 --> 00:13:27,875
It is truly ridiculous and pathetic.

165
00:13:30,415 --> 00:13:33,395
You are wrong, Official Mu.

166
00:13:33,395 --> 00:13:35,335
Even if a sparrow has the ambition of a swan,

167
00:13:35,336 --> 00:13:37,515
it won't be strong enough to fly up high in the sky.

168
00:13:37,515 --> 00:13:39,455
One's destiny is fixed.

169
00:13:39,456 --> 00:13:42,295
How can the silt rise above the clouds?

170
00:13:42,295 --> 00:13:44,076
Rise above?

171
00:13:44,076 --> 00:13:45,574
I'm afraid what you said was wrong.

172
00:13:45,575 --> 00:13:48,654
Everything I have today was earned on my own.

173
00:13:48,655 --> 00:13:53,435
Besides, to me, my career as an official

174
00:13:53,435 --> 00:13:55,535
always comes first.

175
00:13:57,535 --> 00:13:59,656
- Lord Ding. 
 - My Lord.

176
00:14:02,695 --> 00:14:06,095
I know that I have no place in your heart,

177
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:09,475
but you don't have to emphasize it all the time.

178
00:14:48,695 --> 00:14:49,974
Official Mu.

179
00:14:49,974 --> 00:14:51,775
What a coincidence.

180
00:14:58,715 --> 00:15:03,134
My Lord, we must set some rules from now on.

181
00:15:03,134 --> 00:15:05,095
All right.

182
00:15:05,095 --> 00:15:07,574
Act appropriately in front of others.

183
00:15:07,575 --> 00:15:10,054
We can't let them find out about our relationship.

184
00:15:10,055 --> 00:15:12,595
My Lord is so clever.

185
00:15:12,595 --> 00:15:14,655
I'm returning to my duty.

186
00:15:21,532 --> 00:15:23,927
   

187
00:15:34,496 --> 00:15:36,895
Was this also sent to other places

188
00:15:36,895 --> 00:15:39,156
or am I the only one getting it?

189
00:15:39,156 --> 00:15:43,236
Officials of Six Ministries don't have it, to say the least.

190
00:16:03,216 --> 00:16:05,016
Thank you.

191
00:16:11,096 --> 00:16:14,796
My Lord, Ministry of Personnel extended their thanks.

192
00:16:14,796 --> 00:16:17,936
Ministry of Justice, Ministry of Rites,

193
00:16:17,936 --> 00:16:21,116
Ministry of War, and Ministry of Works as well.

194
00:16:23,336 --> 00:16:24,635
And the Ministry of Revenue?

195
00:16:24,635 --> 00:16:26,976
Did they send someone to say thanks?

196
00:16:27,736 --> 00:16:31,116
The cost of the ice was appropriated from them.

197
00:16:31,116 --> 00:16:33,096
Minister Xu feels upset over it.

198
00:16:33,096 --> 00:16:35,123
He probably won't come.

199
00:16:39,496 --> 00:16:42,235
Anything can be solved, as danger is nothing to be afraid of.

200
00:16:42,235 --> 00:16:46,035
Is this what the Ministry of Revenue thinks of the disaster in Jiangnan?

201
00:16:46,035 --> 00:16:47,995
Tell me what you think.

202
00:16:48,895 --> 00:16:51,356
The locust plague was cruel,

203
00:16:51,356 --> 00:16:53,796
but you are wise, My Lord.

204
00:16:53,796 --> 00:16:57,035
You are not making any sense.

205
00:16:57,035 --> 00:16:58,836
Next.

206
00:16:58,836 --> 00:17:01,936
I think there is nothing wrong with that remark.

207
00:17:01,936 --> 00:17:06,916
Thanks to your decisive judgment, we were able to overcome the crisis.

208
00:17:06,916 --> 00:17:10,582
It's also a blessing in disguise for the people of Jiangnan.

209
00:17:10,582 --> 00:17:12,015
Full of flattery.

210
00:17:12,016 --> 00:17:13,795
Not a word is sincere.

211
00:17:14,535 --> 00:17:16,035
Next.

212
00:17:16,896 --> 00:17:20,655
We will do as you say, My Lord.

213
00:17:20,656 --> 00:17:25,155
No one from the Ministry of Revenue can make things clear.

214
00:17:25,155 --> 00:17:28,475
I will go and figure something out.

215
00:17:31,295 --> 00:17:33,736
What am I supposed to do?

216
00:17:33,736 --> 00:17:35,775
Official Li, how did it go? Is His Lordship happy?

217
00:17:35,775 --> 00:17:38,454
Happy? Far from it!

218
00:17:57,515 --> 00:17:59,215
Official Li.

219
00:17:59,855 --> 00:18:01,955
Official Mu.

220
00:18:01,955 --> 00:18:06,656
The hopes of the Ministry of Revenue all lie with you now.

221
00:18:08,656 --> 00:18:11,655
I don't know what is going on with Lord Ding today.

222
00:18:11,656 --> 00:18:13,636
He's so cranky.

223
00:18:13,636 --> 00:18:15,334
He's unhappy with everything.

224
00:18:15,335 --> 00:18:17,795
He keeps torturing us.

225
00:18:18,335 --> 00:18:20,574
We have appropriated funds for the ice today.

226
00:18:20,575 --> 00:18:23,676
Why is he always giving us such a hard time?

227
00:18:24,496 --> 00:18:29,276
That's why we have no choice but to send you to deal with him.

228
00:18:30,496 --> 00:18:32,836
Me?

229
00:18:32,836 --> 00:18:35,052
   

230
00:18:39,055 --> 00:18:40,895
Is he in a bad mood?

231
00:19:00,456 --> 00:19:01,854
My Lord.

232
00:19:01,855 --> 00:19:05,515
It took them long enough to send you here.

233
00:19:05,515 --> 00:19:09,295
What are your thoughts on the disaster relief for Jiangnan?

234
00:19:12,020 --> 00:19:15,320
Disasters don't come out of nowhere. Blessings don't fall from the sky.

235
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:16,935
This is what I think.

236
00:19:16,936 --> 00:19:20,735
The disaster in Jiangnan was both natural and man-made.

237
00:19:20,736 --> 00:19:22,556
But isn't it a good thing for the people

238
00:19:22,556 --> 00:19:29,095
if corrupted and greedy officials were weeded out because of this?

239
00:19:35,715 --> 00:19:37,015
Yes.

240
00:19:37,015 --> 00:19:39,056
No one says it better than you.

241
00:19:40,295 --> 00:19:43,155
You have had a hard time writing documents lately.

242
00:19:45,295 --> 00:19:46,094
Come.

243
00:19:46,095 --> 00:19:47,695
Come on.

244
00:19:50,696 --> 00:19:53,135
I've been waiting for you to eat.

245
00:19:53,135 --> 00:19:56,315
I'm still on duty. I have to go back and tidy up.

246
00:19:56,315 --> 00:19:58,235
Eating is also an important matter.

247
00:19:59,896 --> 00:20:01,215
My Lord,

248
00:20:01,216 --> 00:20:04,434
you have caused the Ministry of Revenue to be in a panic today.

249
00:20:04,434 --> 00:20:05,854
That's good.

250
00:20:05,855 --> 00:20:09,635
This way, they will learn that brown-nosing won't solve the problem.

251
00:20:09,635 --> 00:20:11,576
Then they will always send you here.

252
00:20:14,696 --> 00:20:18,095
After all, I am just your secret lover.

253
00:20:18,095 --> 00:20:22,316
I cannot be with you in public.

254
00:20:23,416 --> 00:20:27,556
All right. My Lord has suffered.

255
00:20:31,736 --> 00:20:33,336
Are you happy now?

256
00:20:33,336 --> 00:20:35,075
I'm not upset anymore.

257
00:20:36,176 --> 00:20:37,876
Have some more.

258
00:21:01,936 --> 00:21:04,215
My Lord, I'm done eating.

259
00:21:04,216 --> 00:21:06,216
I have to go now.

260
00:21:06,216 --> 00:21:08,116
So soon?

261
00:21:09,535 --> 00:21:13,435
Once I am off duty, I'll wait for you outside.

262
00:21:13,435 --> 00:21:17,215
I'll bring back the document, tidy up for a bit, and come out.

263
00:21:34,976 --> 00:21:37,954
This step forward that His Lordship took is such a big step.

264
00:21:37,954 --> 00:21:40,116
We should learn from him.

265
00:21:49,496 --> 00:21:50,895
Official Wen.

266
00:21:50,896 --> 00:21:52,596
It's been a while.

267
00:21:54,135 --> 00:21:57,816
What brings you to the Ministry of Revenue?

268
00:21:58,456 --> 00:22:01,154
Not long ago, good scholars were being appointed.

269
00:22:01,154 --> 00:22:04,656
I was chosen to be a political observer here.

270
00:22:04,656 --> 00:22:07,814
Well, not only are we from the same batch, but we're also colleagues.

271
00:22:07,815 --> 00:22:10,675
Please look out for me in the future.

272
00:22:10,675 --> 00:22:12,695
You're being too humble, Official Mu.

273
00:22:12,695 --> 00:22:15,476
Now, you are the Director of the Ministry of Revenue,

274
00:22:15,476 --> 00:22:18,415
while I'm just a low-ranking political observer.

275
00:22:18,416 --> 00:22:20,175
I'm in no place to act superior.

276
00:22:20,176 --> 00:22:22,416
If that's the case, not long ago,

277
00:22:22,417 --> 00:22:23,975
I was a low-ranking political observer, too.

278
00:22:23,976 --> 00:22:25,534
I am ashamed of myself.

279
00:22:25,535 --> 00:22:26,895
Why are you ashamed?

280
00:22:26,896 --> 00:22:32,276
Because you are a man, but your ranking isn't as high as mine?

281
00:22:34,936 --> 00:22:36,536
I...

282
00:22:36,536 --> 00:22:42,214
I was sort of pedantic in the past over the difference between men and women.

283
00:22:42,216 --> 00:22:46,356
I am truly... truly sorry.

284
00:22:46,356 --> 00:22:48,094
Just admit your wrongs and change.

285
00:22:48,095 --> 00:22:50,396
Bowing to me is unnecessary.

286
00:22:55,615 --> 00:22:57,795
I should get going.

287
00:22:58,335 --> 00:23:01,535
Official Mu. Official Mu.

288
00:23:04,535 --> 00:23:07,696
Official Mu, are you married?

289
00:23:08,596 --> 00:23:11,456
She is really popular with men.

290
00:23:15,335 --> 00:23:20,115
According to the law of Southern Chen, women can marry once they are 16.

291
00:23:20,115 --> 00:23:24,255
Have your elders in the family made any arrangements for you?

292
00:23:26,496 --> 00:23:30,995
I'm dedicated to serving my nation with no intention to marry.

293
00:23:34,135 --> 00:23:37,335
In that case, I will be frank.

294
00:23:40,936 --> 00:23:45,955
What do you think of me?

295
00:23:51,176 --> 00:23:54,175
Well, you are a gentleman.

296
00:23:54,176 --> 00:23:58,995
I have always respected you like an elder brother.

297
00:23:59,515 --> 00:24:02,075
Indeed, I am slightly older than you.

298
00:24:02,075 --> 00:24:04,094
But I wouldn't claim myself as your brother.

299
00:24:04,095 --> 00:24:08,856
A few days ago, I thought you and Official Shen were...

300
00:24:10,295 --> 00:24:12,916
I found out it was a misunderstanding later on.

301
00:24:12,916 --> 00:24:19,016
That's why I made a bold confession to you today.

302
00:24:19,775 --> 00:24:21,275
I...

303
00:24:25,656 --> 00:24:28,954
- Greetings, Lord Ding. 
 - Greetings, Lord Ding.

304
00:24:28,954 --> 00:24:30,616
Be at ease.

305
00:24:32,176 --> 00:24:33,835
It's already late.

306
00:24:33,835 --> 00:24:36,996
Is the Ministry of Revenue still working?

307
00:24:36,996 --> 00:24:40,155
Your Lordship, we were just about to leave.

308
00:24:40,155 --> 00:24:42,256
You may leave first.

309
00:24:42,256 --> 00:24:44,716
I have something important to discuss with Official Mu.

310
00:24:59,256 --> 00:25:02,094
My Lord, I didn't want this to happen.

311
00:25:02,094 --> 00:25:03,916
I know that.

312
00:25:07,896 --> 00:25:09,334
I have an idea.

313
00:25:09,335 --> 00:25:11,574
It will stop him from bothering you.

314
00:25:11,575 --> 00:25:13,375
What is it?

315
00:25:13,375 --> 00:25:15,315
Cater to his taste.

316
00:25:15,315 --> 00:25:17,315
Make him distant himself.

317
00:25:17,315 --> 00:25:19,916
Well, I'm counting on you, My Lord.

318
00:25:23,750 --> 00:25:26,393
   

319
00:25:29,016 --> 00:25:30,516
Official Mu.

320
00:25:32,095 --> 00:25:33,595
Official Mu.

321
00:25:37,496 --> 00:25:38,896
Official Mu,

322
00:25:38,896 --> 00:25:42,334
have you considered what I said to you the other day?

323
00:25:42,335 --> 00:25:45,215
I... Official Wen,

324
00:25:45,216 --> 00:25:48,436
I have made it clear that day.

325
00:25:48,436 --> 00:25:51,216
I really have no intention to marry.

326
00:25:52,055 --> 00:25:53,555
Look.

327
00:25:53,555 --> 00:25:56,054
Marriage is a natural thing.

328
00:25:56,055 --> 00:25:58,375
How can a woman not marry?

329
00:25:59,216 --> 00:26:01,016
To tell you the truth,

330
00:26:01,016 --> 00:26:06,295
the elders in the family often say that a woman without talent is virtuous.

331
00:26:06,295 --> 00:26:08,796
I initially thought so, too.

332
00:26:08,796 --> 00:26:12,735
But ever since I heard of what you did in Jiangnan,

333
00:26:12,735 --> 00:26:14,576
I changed my mind.

334
00:26:15,535 --> 00:26:19,935
I think women should be like you.

335
00:26:19,935 --> 00:26:21,774
Well-educated and well-mannered.

336
00:26:21,775 --> 00:26:24,355
Be exceptionalin both appearance and intellect.

337
00:26:25,135 --> 00:26:27,735
You are fine-looking and talented.

338
00:26:27,736 --> 00:26:30,054
But I don't share your feelings.

339
00:26:30,055 --> 00:26:34,175
I really have no intention to marry.

340
00:26:36,896 --> 00:26:38,396
Official Mu,

341
00:26:38,396 --> 00:26:42,695
if you think I'm not good enough for you, just be frank with me.

342
00:26:42,696 --> 00:26:45,896
If I can improve it, I will change it for you.

343
00:26:45,896 --> 00:26:47,094
Not at all.

344
00:26:47,095 --> 00:26:49,054
You are not lacking in any way.

345
00:26:49,055 --> 00:26:53,415
It's just that I... I am not good enough for you.

346
00:26:53,416 --> 00:26:55,175
Not at all.

347
00:26:55,175 --> 00:26:56,895
I think...

348
00:26:57,696 --> 00:27:00,516
I think you are incredible.

349
00:27:00,516 --> 00:27:05,408
If we get married, we can surely help each other.

350
00:27:05,409 --> 00:27:09,294
- Greetings, Lord Ding. 
 - Greetings, Lord Ding.

351
00:27:09,896 --> 00:27:11,296
Official Mu.

352
00:27:12,936 --> 00:27:15,516
I have work to assign you.

353
00:27:15,516 --> 00:27:17,296
Come with me.

354
00:27:18,936 --> 00:27:20,536
Yes, My Lord.

355
00:27:33,896 --> 00:27:35,596
My Lord.

356
00:27:36,615 --> 00:27:42,294
My Lord, I thought you said you had an idea to stop Wen Shizong from bothering me.

357
00:27:42,294 --> 00:27:44,235
What exactly is it?

358
00:27:46,295 --> 00:27:48,415
What if you have offended me?

359
00:27:49,936 --> 00:27:51,976
Will he dare marry you?

360
00:27:56,416 --> 00:27:59,056
You have shut the door so tightly.

361
00:27:59,056 --> 00:28:01,156
Others can barely see a thing.

362
00:28:02,235 --> 00:28:04,455
It would be best.

363
00:28:07,815 --> 00:28:09,596
I think so, too.

